<p><b>THE SOCK DRIVE NUMBERS ARE IN!</b> St. James
parishioners donated a total of 2,632 pairs of socks
during Advent! Socks go to organizations that work to
directly empower people experiencing homelessness
such as St. Francis House, Urban Rest Stop, St. Martin
de Porres Shelter, Lazarus Day Center, and our
Cathedral’s own Solanus Casey Center, Cathedral
Kitchen, and Foot Care. Thank you for your generous
support!</p>
<p><b>THE ESPRESSO MINISTRY</b> is up and running after the
10:00am Mass. This month, all espresso sales benefit
our Mental Health Ministry.</p>
<p><b>PARISH REMEMBRANCE</b>: <i>Throughout the year, because we
are the Cathedral Church, we remember in prayer at Mass
and Vespers each of the parishes and missions of the
Archdiocese of Seattle on a Sunday near their feast day</i>. This
week we remember in prayer the parishes of St. Paul in
Seattle and on the Swinomish Reservation, and the St. Paul
Mission in Westport.</p>

